rComments: It was hard to understand her. She was teaching in French (which is NOT her first language and maybe not even her second. However, she is very helpful when you ask questions. She knows her stuff but there is a language barrier. Over all: Great person, mediocre teaching. If the class was taught in English it would have made all the difference!

This class is a disaster. She can not speak french to save her life. All she does is read a million sheets of paper. She posts her slides online, but they are very difficult to understand. Very poor in french grammar.Her powerpoints are just an infinate amount of statistics. She is a very nice person, but she shouldnt be teaching people in french

She was really hard to follow sometimes! All she did was read numbers from her endless sheets. She did nothing but read us her lecture notes. Then we watched outdated movies about women's issues! The films she showed were so old and irrelevant! It was hard to concentrate in her class when all she did was read stats from her page!
She's lovely. Kind and open, and really knows her stuff.
Boring Boring Borign lecturer.  Sits in a chair and reads right off her paper.

I walked into this class on the first day and left 45 mins later.  Her expectations for a 2nd yr class are ridiculous.  You had about 4 papers, discussion groups and a presentation.  It was more like a fourth year of graduate level course. She was also a bit arrogant, warning not to plagerize because she was so well read.  What professor isn't?
she gets so worked up about science! It's unlike anything you'll ever see!
